==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lunation
<hw>Lu*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Lunated</er>.]</ety> <def>The period of a synodic revolution of the
moon, or the time from one new moon to the next; varying in length, at
different times, from about 29⟦frac14⟧ to 29⟦frac56⟧ days, the average
length being 29 d., 12h., 44m., 2.9s.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lunch</ent>⟦br⟧
